# Publish and Deploy Conventions

## Publish Profile

- `Properties/PublishProfiles/WinApp.pubxml` — self-contained win-x64 Release build
- Output: `bin\Release\net10.0-windows\win-x64\publish\`

## Build Script

`Build-And-Publish.ps1` at project root handles the full pipeline:

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "Build-And-Publish.ps1"                  # Patch bump
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "Build-And-Publish.ps1" -VersionPart Minor
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "Build-And-Publish.ps1" -VersionPart Major
```

## Version Management

All three files are kept in sync:

| File | Property |
|------|----------|
| `DbExplorer.csproj` | `<Version>`, `<AssemblyVersion>`, `<FileVersion>` |
| `DbExplorerTray\DbExplorerTray.csproj` | `<Version>`, `<AssemblyVersion>`, `<FileVersion>` |
| `DbExplorer.Installer\Package.wxs` | `Version="x.y.z"` on `<Package>` |

## MSI Installer

- WiX project: `DbExplorer.Installer\DbExplorer.Installer.wixproj`
- Output: `DbExplorer.Installer\bin\x64\Release\DbExplorer.Setup.msi`
- Consumes published files from `bin\Release\net10.0-windows\win-x64\publish\`

## Deploy Target

MSI is copied to: `\\t-no1fkxtst-app\FkCommon\Software\WindowsApps\DbExplorer`

## Code Signing

- Signing only runs for FK users (username starts with `FK`)
- Sign script: `\\t-no1fkxtst-app.fknett.fk.no\FkCommon\Software\FkPshApps\FkSign\FkSign.ps1`
- Both EXE (via csproj PostBuild) and MSI (via wixproj SignMsi target) are signed in Release
